function vest(address beneficiary) external {
    require(block.timestamp >= vestingEnd);
    uint256 amount = allocations[beneficiary];
    allocations[beneficiary] = 0;
    token.transfer(beneficiary, amount);
}

chosen:
**Vulnerability: Anyone Can Trigger Vesting for Any Address**

There is no check that `msg.sender == beneficiary`. Any address can call `vest(victim)` and force-claim the vested tokens on behalf of anyone. While the tokens go to `beneficiary`, this could break integrations (e.g. if the beneficiary is a smart contract that needs to handle the tokens in a specific way).

**Fix:**
```solidity
function vest() external {
    require(block.timestamp >= vestingEnd, "not yet");
    uint256 amount = allocations[msg.sender];
    require(amount > 0, "nothing to claim");
    allocations[msg.sender] = 0;
    token.transfer(msg.sender, amount);
}
```

