function stake(uint256 amount) external {
    stakedBalance[msg.sender] += amount;
    totalStaked += amount;
    rewardDebt[msg.sender] = stakedBalance[msg.sender] * accRewardPerShare / 1e12;
}

chosen:
**Vulnerability: Missing Token Transfer**

The function updates internal accounting (`stakedBalance`, `totalStaked`, `rewardDebt`) but never calls `token.transferFrom(msg.sender, address(this), amount)`. A user can call `stake(1e18)` and receive credit for 1e18 tokens without transferring any, inflating their balance and claiming all rewards.

**Fix:**
```solidity
function stake(uint256 amount) external {
    require(amount > 0, "zero amount");
    token.transferFrom(msg.sender, address(this), amount);
    _updateRewards(msg.sender);
    stakedBalance[msg.sender] += amount;
    totalStaked += amount;
    rewardDebt[msg.sender] = stakedBalance[msg.sender] * accRewardPerShare / 1e12;
}
```

